## Early game

**Wahiba** on Mars (Dark Sector Survival) is an easy early Salvage source —
Mars is one of Salvage's three signature planets, and this low-level Dark
Sector node is safe to run before a squad is fully geared. Salvage has no
dedicated enemy drop table, so the wiki's own advice applies here too:
"endless missions have a higher concentration of mobs and also a decent
amount of storage containers and lockers," and it's those containers, not the
mobs, that actually drop Salvage.

## Mid & late game

**Carme** on Jupiter (Mobile Defense) is the wiki's standout late-game pick,
citing up to 3,000 Salvage in a single run if every container and locker in
the Corpus tileset gets opened. Since Salvage is still a container-based
pickup rather than an enemy drop, Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path
passive don't add anything on top — a squad that splits up and loots
thoroughly will out-farm one that just fights through to the objective.
**Elara** (Survival), also on Jupiter, is a solid endless alternative with a
Nekros or other loot-enhancing frame along for the ride.

